Revision history for DBIO-MySQL

{{$NEXT}}
    - Add apply_limit() to DBIO::MySQL::SQLMaker (LIMIT ?, ? syntax)
    - Remove sql_limit_dialect from Storage (limit logic now in SQLMaker)
    - Declare DateTime::Format::MySQL as a runtime dependency
    - Add AccessBroker connect smoke coverage for MySQL storage
    - Move PEEPEENESS test usage to DBIO::Util
    - Add deploy_defaults() and deploy_setup() to MySQL::Storage so drivers
      declare their own test-deploy requirements (add_drop_table, sql_mode fixup)
    - Add native Introspect/Diff/DDL/Deploy modules (parallel to the
      DBIO::PostgreSQL and DBIO::SQLite sets). Replaces the SQL::Translator
      path for schema deployment and diffing:
        . DBIO::MySQL::Introspect (+ Tables, Columns, Indexes,
          ForeignKeys) via information_schema
        . DBIO::MySQL::DDL generator from Result classes with
          ENGINE/CHARSET/COLLATE handling
        . DBIO::MySQL::Diff (+ Table, Column, Index, ForeignKey) with
          columns inlined on CREATE TABLE and full MODIFY COLUMN support
        . DBIO::MySQL::Deploy with install/diff/apply/upgrade using
          CREATE DATABASE for the test-deploy target
    - Add DBIO::MySQL::Result component with mysql_engine, mysql_charset,
      mysql_collate and mysql_index declarations (consumed by the DDL
      generator)
    - Storage now declares dbio_deploy_class so DBIO::Schema->deploy()
      routes through DBIO::MySQL::Deploy instead of SQL::Translator
    - Remove DBIx::Class backcompat shim 'for => "shared"' from
      MySQL::SQLMaker along with its deprecation warning; use
      'for => "share"' (FOR SHARE) only -- MariaDB, which does not
      support FOR SHARE, goes through DBIO::MySQL::SQLMaker::MariaDB
      instead (below)
    - Add DBIO::MySQL::SQLMaker::MariaDB: MariaDB SQLMaker subclass
      that maps 'for => "share"' to LOCK IN SHARE MODE since MariaDB
      does not implement the FOR SHARE keyword. DBIO::MySQL::Storage::
      MariaDB now declares this class as its sql_maker_class
    - Fix t/10-mysql.t MariaDB detection: use SELECT VERSION() directly
      instead of _server_info->{dbms_version} which may not include
      the "MariaDB" suffix depending on DBD flavor
    - Drop legacy SchemaVersions -> dbix_class_schema_versions migration
      steps from t/30-versioning.t (core no longer supports the
      transition) and update table name to dbio_schema_versions
    - t/21-datetime-mysql.t now deploys with add_drop_table => 1 so it
      can run in sequence with other tests that share the test database
    - Remove all "package # hide from PAUSE" tricks from test helper
      result classes
    - Remove workspace .proverc (tests run against installed dbio core
      via dzil install)
    - Add t/40-diff.t (33 unit tests covering all Diff modules and the
      orchestrator) and t/41-introspect-load.t (12 module load tests)
